"Lu J., Yu L., Zhang X., Zhang S., Dai W.","Hydrogen production from a fluidized-bed coal gasifier with in situ fixation of CO2 Part I: Numerical model",2008,"Chemical Engineering and Technology","31","2",,"197","207",,,10.1002/ceat.200700380,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-39549116929&partnerID=40&md5=c55d0d110756efde7bbcb7734964d662","State Key Laboratory of Multiphase Complex Systems, Chinese Academy of Sciences, Beijing 100080, China; China Graduate University, Chinese Academy of Sciences, Beijing, China; Advanced Systems Center, Mitsubishi Materials Corporation, Tokyo, Japan","Lu, J., State Key Laboratory of Multiphase Complex Systems, Chinese Academy of Sciences, Beijing 100080, China, China Graduate University, Chinese Academy of Sciences, Beijing, China; Yu, L., State Key Laboratory of Multiphase Complex Systems, Chinese Academy of Sciences, Beijing 100080, China, China Graduate University, Chinese Academy of Sciences, Beijing, China; Zhang, X., State Key Laboratory of Multiphase Complex Systems, Chinese Academy of Sciences, Beijing 100080, China; Zhang, S., State Key Laboratory of Multiphase Complex Systems, Chinese Academy of Sciences, Beijing 100080, China; Dai, W., Advanced Systems Center, Mitsubishi Materials Corporation, Tokyo, Japan","In order to attempt to eliminate global warming effects, it is highly desirable that new technologies with lower or zero emission of CO2 to the environment are developed. In this work, a high-pressure fluidized-bed coal gasifier for H2 production with in situ fixation of CO2 is simulated by a comprehensive two-dimensional model. The Eddy Dissipation Concept (EDC) model is first adopted in the pulverized coal gasification model to simultaneously describe the turbulent mixing and detailed chemical kinetics. The developed model is verified with experimental results. The simulated concentrations for the gas product agree well with the experimental data. The simulated distributions for gas temperature and velocity correlate well with the reaction mechanism and experimental phenomena. © 2008 Wiley-VCH Verlag GmbH &amp; Co. KGaA, Weinheim.","Carbon dioxide; Gasification; Hydrogen; Simulation","Carbon dioxide; Computer simulation; Fluidized bed process; Hydrogen production; Mathematical models; Mixing; Reaction kinetics; Fluidized-bed coal gasifier; In situ fixation; Turbulent mixing; Coal gasification; Carbon dioxide; Coal gasification; Computer simulation; Fluidized bed process; Hydrogen production; Mathematical models; Mixing; Reaction kinetics",,,,,,"Kuramoto, K., (2003) Fuel Process. Technol, 82, p. 61; Wang, J., Takarada, T., (2001) Energy Fuels, 15, p. 356; Lin, S.Y., Suzuki, Y., Hatano, H., Harada, M., (2001) Energy Fuels, 15, p. 339; Lin, S., Harada, M., Suzuki, Y., Hatano, H., (2004) Fuel, 83, p. 869; Lin, S., Harada, M., Suzuki, Y., Hatano, H., (2006) Fuel, 85, p. 1143; Lin, S., Harada, A., Suzuki, Y., Hatano, H., (2005) Energy Conversion Manage, 46, p. 869; Wen, C.Y., Chaung, T.Z., (1979) Ind. Eng. Chem. Process Des. Dev, 18 (4), p. 684; Govind, R., Shah, J., (1984) AIChE J, 30 (1), p. 79; Chen, C., Horio, M., Kojima, T., (2000) Chem. Eng. Sci, 55, p. 3861; Smoot, L.D., Smith, P.J., (1985) Coal Combustion and Gasification, , Plenum Press, New York; Hill, S.C., Smoot, L.D., (1993) Energy Fuels, 7, p. 874; Watanabe, H., Otaka, M., (2006) Fuel, 85, p. 1935; Han, C.C., (2000) Int. J. Energy Res, 24, p. 511; Yu, L., Lu, J., Zhang, X., Zhang, S., (2007) Fuel, 86, p. 722; Vicente, W., Ochoa, S., Aguillon, J., Barrios, E., (1993) Appl. Therm. Eng, 2003, p. 23; Choi, Y.C., (2001) Fuel, 80, p. 2193; Zhou, L.X., Zhang, Y., Zhang, J., (2003) Fuel, 82, p. 1001; Zhang, Y., Wei, X.L., Zhou, L.X., Sheng, H.Z., (2005) Fuel, 84, p. 1798; Guo, Y.C., Chan, C.K., Lau, K.S., (2003) Fuel, 82, p. 893; Chen, X.L., Zhou, L.X., Zhang, J., (2000) Acta Mechanica Sinica, 16, p. 41; Zhou, L.X., (1991) Simulation of Two-Phase Turbulent Flow and Combustion, , Tsing Hua University Press, Bei